@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Author Guidelines & Manuscript Template";
}

<div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-md-9">
        <h2 class="section-title">Author Guidelines</h2>
        
        <p class="text-muted mb-4">Please read this guide carefully to format your manuscript prior to submission. Submissions that do not adhere to these standards will be returned by the editor.</p>

        <h4 class="font-weight-bold text-dark mt-4" style="font-family: var(--serif-font);">1. Manuscript Preparation</h4>
        <p>All papers must be written in English. Manuscripts must be formatted in a single-column layout using a standard serif font (12pt, e.g., Times New Roman). Margins should be set to 1 inch on all sides. All pages must be numbered consecutively.</p>

        <h4 class="font-weight-bold text-dark mt-4" style="font-family: var(--serif-font);">2. Double-Blind Peer Review Compliance</h4>
        <div class="alert alert-warning">
            <strong>CRITICAL REQUIREMENT:</strong> To comply with our double-blind review process, authors must remove all identifying information from the uploaded PDF manuscript. This includes author names, affiliations, email addresses, and acknowledgements. These details are stored separately in the submission forms.
        </div>

        <h4 class="font-weight-bold text-dark mt-4" style="font-family: var(--serif-font);">3. File Format & Size</h4>
        <p>Manuscripts must be submitted as a single **PDF document**. The maximum allowed file size is 20 MB. Code repositories, high-resolution media, and supplementary datasets should be linked to external public vaults (like GitHub or Zenodo).</p>

        <h4 class="font-weight-bold text-dark mt-4" style="font-family: var(--serif-font);">4. Reference & Citation Style</h4>
        <p>Authors must follow the **IEEE reference style**. In-text citations should be numbered sequentially in square brackets, e.g., [1]. The references section at the end of the paper should list citations in alphabetical/numerical order matching their occurrence.</p>
    </div>
</div>
